## Summary

Variable IMember is converted to JSON schema with properties and required fields

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "id": {"type": "string", "format": "uuid"},
    "name": {"type": "string"},
    "email": {"type": "string", "format": "email"},
    "age": {"type": "number", "minimum": 20, "exclusiveMaximum": 100},
    "hobbies": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "id": {"type": "string", "format": "uuid"},
          "name": {"type": "string"}
        },
        "required": ["id", "name"]
      }
    },
    "created_at": {"type": "string", "format": "date-time"},
    "updated_at": {"type": "string", "format": "date-time"},
    "deleted_at": {"type": ["null", "string"], "format": "date-time"}
  },
  "required": ["id", "name", "email", "age", "hobbies", "created_at", "updated_at", "deleted_at"]
}
```

This json schema collection is collected using "collectSchema" method with input:

```ts
{
  schema: {
    "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
    type: "object",
    properties: {
      id: { type: "string", format: "uuid" },
      name: { type: "string" },
      email: { type: "string", format: "email" },
      age: { type: "number", minimum: 20, exclusiveMaximum: 100 },
      hobbies: {
        type: "array",
        items: {
          type: "object",
          properties: {
            id: { type: "string", format: "uuid" },
            name: { type: "string" },
          },
          required: ["id", "name"],
        },
      },
      created_at: { type: "string", format: "date-time" },
      updated_at: { type: "string", format: "date-time" },
      deleted_at: { type: ['null', 'string'], format: 'date-time' }
    },
    required: [
      "id", "name", "email", "age", "hobbies", "created_at", "updated_at", "deleted_at"
    ]
  }
}
```

```json
{

    "type": "object",

      "id": {
        "type": "string",
        "format": "uuid"

      "name": {

      },
      "email": {
        "type": "string",
        "format": "email"
      },
      "age": {
        "type": "number",
        "minimum": 20,
        "exclusiveMaximum": 100
      },
      "hobbies": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "id": {
              "type": "string",
              "format": "uuid"
            },
            "name": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "required": ["id", "name"]
        }
      },
      "created_at": {
        "type": "string",
        "format": "date-time"
      },
      "updated_at": {
        "type": "string",
        "format": "date-time"
      },
      "deleted_at": {
        "type": ["null", "string"],
        "format": "date-time"
      }
    },
    "required": ["id", "name", "email", "age", "hobbies", "created_at", "updated_at", "deleted_at"]
  }
}
```\n
This JSON schema represents the `IMember` interface with all its properties and constraints. The `required` array specifies which fields must be present in a valid object of this schema. The `hobbies` property is an array of objects, each with `id` and `name` properties, and the schema enforces that both properties are required for each hobby item. The `age` property has constraints on its minimum and exclusive maximum values. The `deleted_at` field is optional and can either be null or a date-time string. The formats for various fields like `id`, `email`, and date-time fields are also specified. This schema can be reused in other parts of the application or shared with other systems that need to validate or process `IMember` data. The schema follows the draft-07 version of JSON Schema. The `required` fields are marked to ensure that any object adhering to this schema must include these properties. The `additionalItems` is set to false for the `hobbies` array to prevent additional items beyond those defined in the schema. The collection of this schema can be reused by referencing its schema object or by importing the JSON schema document in other contexts where the `IMember` data structure is expected.

Laditionalitems è impostato su falso per il array hobbies per prevenire elementi aggiuntivi oltre quelli definiti nello schema.
